## Takeaway

The key idea is to maintain a **Monotonic Decreasing Stack** of **(price, span)** pairs. Whenever a new price arrives, all previous prices that are smaller than or equal to it are removed, and their spans are added to the current span. This avoids repeated comparisons and allows every stock price to be processed only once, resulting in an efficient **O(n)** solution.
